1 the home of a child’s guardian; establishing the Office of the Child Welfare
2 Ombudsman in the Office of the Attorney General; exempting from disclosure under
3 the Maryland Public Information Act records related to certain complaints;
4 prohibiting a person from certain willful interference and discriminatory and
5 retaliatory acts relating to complaints filed with the Office; and generally relating to
6 child protection and the Office of the Child Welfare Ombudsman the Guardianship
7 Assistance Program and the State Foster Youth Ombudsman.
