14 Preamble
15 WHEREAS, Child abuse and neglect is a serious and reprehensible problem in
16 society; and
17 WHEREAS, The protection of children from abuse and neglect by applying
18 prevention measures and observing best practices in treating children who are abused and
19 neglected must be one of Maryland’s highest public policy priorities; and
20 WHEREAS, The child welfare system must protect and serve Maryland’s children in
21 a manner that keeps them safe and healthy and promotes their well–being; and
22 WHEREAS, The children and families served by the child welfare system, as well as
23 the public, must have a high level of confidence that the system will act in a child’s best
24 interests and will respond to the child’s needs in a timely and professional manner; and
25 WHEREAS, To engender this high level of confidence in the child welfare system, it
26 is important that children and families who become involved in the system, mandatory
27 reporters, and the general public have a well–publicized, easily accessible, and transparent
28 complaint process for voicing concerns regarding the child welfare system along with the
29 expectation that those concerns, once voiced, will be heard and addressed in a timely and
30 appropriate manner; and
31 WHEREAS, To improve child welfare outcomes and to foster best practices, there
32 must be effective accountability mechanisms, including the review and evaluation of
33 concerns voiced by children and families, mandatory reporters, persons involved in the
34 child welfare system, and members of the general public, that provide policymakers with
35 the information necessary to formulate systemic changes, where appropriate; now,
36 therefore,

