18 INDICATED.
19 (2) “GUARDIANSHIP ASSISTANCE” MEANS MONETARY AND MEDICAL
20 ASSISTANCE PROVIDED UNDER THE PROGRAM.
21 (3) “PROGRAM” MEANS THE GUARDIANSHIP ASSISTANCE PROGRAM.
22 (B) THE SECRETARY OF HUMAN SERVICES SHALL ESTABLISH AND
23 MAINTAIN A GUARDIANSHIP ASSISTANCE PROGRAM TO PROMOTE THE PLACEMENT
24 AND MAINTENANCE OF CHILDREN IN PERMANENT GUARDIANSHIP HOMES BY
25 PROVIDING GUARDIANSHIP ASSISTANCE TO GUARDIANS OF MINOR CHILDREN.
26 (C) A GUARDIAN OF A MINOR CHILD MAY BE ELIGIBLE FOR GUARDIANSHIP
27 ASSISTANCE IF:
28 (1) THE GUARDIAN IS APPOINTED UNDER § 5–326 OF THIS TITLE OR §
29 3–819.2 OF THE COURTS ARTICLE;

HOUSE BILL 980 5
1 (2) THE MINOR CHILD IS PLACED IN FOSTER CARE IN THE
2 GUARDIAN’S FAMILY HOME AT LEAST 6 CONSECUTIVE MONTHS IMMEDIATELY
3 PRECEDING THE APPOINTMENT AS GUARDIAN; AND
4 (3) THE GUARDIAN ENTERED INTO A WRITTEN VOLUNTARY
5 GUARDIANSHIP ASSISTANCE AGREEMENT WITH A LOCAL DEPARTMENT BEFORE THE
6 APPOINTMENT AS GUARDIAN.
7 (D) ONCE APPROVED, GUARDIANSHIP ASSISTANCE MAY CONTINUE AFTER
8 AN INDIVIDUAL WITH AN APPOINTED GUARDIAN REACHES THE AGE OF 18 YEARS IF
9 THE INDIVIDUAL IS:
10 (1) ATTENDING SCHOOL;
11 (2) EMPLOYED ON AT LEAST A PART–TIME BASIS;
12 (3) PARTICIPATING IN A PROGRAM DESIGNED TO PROMOTE
13 EMPLOYMENT OPPORTUNITIES; OR
14 (4) INCAPABLE OF WORKING DUE TO A DISABILITY.
15 (E) GUARDIANSHIP ASSISTANCE SHALL TERMINATE NOT LATER THAN THE
16 DAY THAT THE INDIVIDUAL WITH THE APPOINTED GUARDIAN REACHES THE AGE OF
17 21 YEARS.
18 (F) (1) LOCAL DEPARTMENTS SHALL ANNUALLY REVIEW THE
19 GUARDIANSHIP ASSISTANCE PROVIDED UNDER THIS SECTION.
20 (2) A LOCAL DEPARTMENT MAY TERMINATE GUARDIANSHIP
21 ASSISTANCE IF THE LOCAL DEPARTMENT DETERMINES, FOLLOWING AN ANNUAL
22 REVIEW, THAT AN ADULT LIVES IN THE GUARDIAN’S HOME AND IS UNDER THE
23 SUPERVISION OF A CRIMINAL COURT FOLLOWING A CONVICTION FOR A CRIME OF
24 VIOLENCE INVOLVING A CHILD VICTIM OR REQUIRED TO REGISTER WITH A
25 SUPERVISING AUTHORITY IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 11–704 OF THE CRIMINAL
26 PROCEDURE ARTICLE.
27 (G) THE SECRETARY OF HUMAN SERVICES SHALL ADOPT REGULATIONS TO
28 CARRY OUT THIS SECTION.
